    <briefdescription>
<para>This class provides a convenient means of passing multiple parameters to <ref refid="classwx_text_ctrl_1ae59dab77ddefd0df3b3b2e6495c43653" kindref="member">wxTextCtrl::EnableProofCheck()</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>By default, i.e. when calling EnableProofCheck() without any parameters, <ref refid="classwx_text_proof_options_1a378717bbce293cc99a87a289342cdb0a" kindref="member">Default()</ref> proof options are used, which enable spelling (but not grammar) checks for the current language.</para>
<para>However it is also possible to customize the options:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">textctrl-&gt;EnableProofCheck(<ref refid="classwx_text_proof_options_1a378717bbce293cc99a87a289342cdb0a" kindref="member">wxTextProofOptions::Default</ref>().Language(</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;fr&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">).GrammarCheck());</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>or disable the all checks entirely:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">textctrl-&gt;EnableProofCheck(wxTextProofOptions::Disable());</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Note that this class has no public constructor, except for the copy constructor, so its objects can only be created using the static factory methods <ref refid="classwx_text_proof_options_1a378717bbce293cc99a87a289342cdb0a" kindref="member">Default()</ref> or Disable().</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classwx_text_ctrl_1ae59dab77ddefd0df3b3b2e6495c43653" kindref="member">wxTextCtrl::EnableProofCheck()</ref>, <ref refid="classwx_text_ctrl_1a2d76825c71aa93fc512c69cd3597de26" kindref="member">wxTextCtrl::GetProofCheckOptions()</ref>.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="since"><para>3.1.6 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
